The United States is expressing support for the people of Niger as they face a challenge to their democracy on the country's 63rd anniversary of independence. The US emphasizes its partnership with Niger based on shared democratic values and support for civilian-led governance. It asserts that the Nigerien people have the right to choose their leaders and that free and fair elections should be respected. The US calls for the immediate release of President Bazoum and his family and the preservation of Niger's hard-earned democracy.